President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Connecticut and authorized federal aid to assist with recovery efforts after severe storms and flooding. The funding will be used for emergency work, repairing or replacing damaged facilities, and implementing hazard mitigation measures. The counties of Fairfield, Middlesex, and New London are specifically mentioned as areas eligible for assistance. Michael L. Parker has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.